RAIL LINE'S SECOND CRASH IN FOUR DAYS KILLS ONE 
An Amtrak passenger train line that runs between Chicago and Indianapolis 
suffered its second crash in four days when a train ran into a truck Sunday, 
killing the truck's driver, state police said. On Wednesday, a train running 
the same line derailed after running into a group of boxcars in Crawfordsville, 
Ind., injuring 30 people. 
